2.  Schneider, C., et al. "Microplastics as a novel environmental disruptor: Impact on the male reproductive system." Reproductive Biology and Endocrinology, 2024. PMID: 12929567
3.  Gvozdíková, R., et al. "Coenzyme Q10, Oxidative Stress, and Male Infertility: A Systematic Review." Antioxidants, 2021. DOI: 10.3390/antiox10081273

### Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

**Q1: How do microplastics affect sperm?**
A1: They can cause inflammation, oxidative stress, and DNA damage within the testes, potentially reducing sperm quality.

**Q2: How can I avoid microplastics in daily life?**
A2: Reduce single-use plastics, choose natural products, and use water filters to minimize exposure.

**Q3: Can antioxidant supplements help sperm quality?**
A3: Yes, Coenzyme Q10 may reduce oxidative stress and improve sperm parameters, but consult a doctor first.

